Justin Bieber. AFP/Lisa O'connor LOS ANGELES - Ferrari has banned singer Justin Bieber from ever buying its cars again. The dealership accuses Bieber of violating car-modification rules. Bieber has reportedly changed the colour of his 2011 F458 Italia to neon blue. READ:Â Justin Bieber caught up in Saudi rights row He also modified it with a Liberty Walk body kit. In 2016, the singer lost his car after partying in Los Angeles and later put it up for a charity auction. Ferrari dictates that an owner cannot sell their car in the first year. It discourages unauthorised modifications.